subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology . This species in named in honor of François Mocquard (
1834–1917
), the herpetologist who described
Xenotyphlops grandidieri
. During his life Mocquard contributed in a substantial way to the knowledge of Malagasy herpetofauna (
Glaw & Vences, 1994
), culminating in his grand systematic synopsis (
Mocquard, 1909
).
